articles.title: Gas prices rise on fears of strikes in Australia - BBC
articles.description: Possible industrial action at a key liquefied natural gas supplier sent European prices 10% higher.
articles.content:
The prospect of a possible strike at a liquefied natural gas (LNG) plant in Australia has pushed wholesale gas prices up in Europe.
